More terrifying than any Star Destroyer are the cunning skills of the Empire&rsquo;s greatest strategic minds! Among many prestigious figures leading the Imperial Navy, one holds a special place: Grand Admiral Thrawn. Any superficial differences between Thrawn, a male Chiss, and his human peers is overshadowed by his extreme cunning combined with his dogged focus on defeating Rebel forces threatening the Empire. Aiding Thrawn are the skilled and capable agents of the Imperial Security Bureau. This secret task force operates in the shadows investigating suspected Rebel activity across the galaxy before moving to quash them. Among their numbers is Alexsandr Kallus, who applies his abilities as a strategist and warrior to hunting rebels across the galaxy&hellip;

Fan favorite villain Grand Admiral Thrawn is not accepting surrenders, but he is bringing his squad to Star Wars: Shatterpoint. Agent Kallus is the featured Secondary Unit and two ISB agents serve as Supporting Units for this Squad pack.

&mdash;description from the publisher

Rumors of an ancient intelligence swirl around the System&hellip;

A legend, half-remembered from the early centuries of settlement, is again being whispered. And the proof of a murderous alien technology may lie waiting within a storm of meteors&hellip;

But you&rsquo;re a shipper, and you&rsquo;ve got no time for schoolyard tales. You gotta work to keep flying.

But what&rsquo;s this? A Distress Call beckons&hellip;

With this Story Expansion, you and your opponent can uncover the secrets of an ancient mystery. Answer Distress Calls, investigate Rumors, and more as you pursue the secret of the Alien Legend. But don&rsquo;t get too wrapped up in the mystery. You still have to earn Credits and Valor to keep your reputation as an independent ship owner.

The Dog Star Shipper's Alien Legend Story Expansion adds an exciting episode to the Dog Star Shippers experience.

&mdash;description from the publisher

Greetings, Townsfolk! Your cosy hamlet recently welcomed three new dragon hatchlings, but there&rsquo;s not enough room for them in the watchtower where mother dragon has chosen to roost. Work together to manipulate the watchtower, to create safe spaces for the baby dragons and to settle the hatchlings in before mother dragon returns&hellip;

Working together, use tools to manipulate a tower of wooden pieces. Create enough space to safely balance 3 baby dragon miniatures before running out of tool actions. Finally, place the mother dragon on top of your tower to win. If any baby dragons fall, you lose (but don&rsquo;t worry; we put up a net to catch them!). Test your skills over dozens of levels with new tower structures and challenge tokens.

&mdash;description from the publisher
